title: 156: The Faust and the Furious 2: Mopey Ol' Stiff
dc:creator: A.J. Hanenburg
description: The rest of Goethe's Faust is flat bananas, and it ends with a devil flirting with Angels. I can't even. (Also, please don't miss my rhyming pun with "Tokyo Drift." I'm convinced puns are extra good if you have to explain them.)
itunes:author: One old couple and a grumpy old sorcerer (Graeme)
itunes:subtitle: Don't ever touch a ghost Helen unless you want your hand exploded.
